template:
Translate the following {fromLanguage} story to {toLanguage}, adapted for {difficulty} CEFR level:

Instructions:
{instructions}

Specific {toLanguage} Guidelines:
{languageInstructions}

{nativeToTargetInstructions}

{fromLanguage} Story:
{text}

RESPONSE FORMAT:
Return a JSON object with the following structure:
{
  "translation": "<full translated story text>",
  "words": [
    {
      "from_word": "<original word>",
      "from_lemma": "<lemma/base form of original word>",
      "to_word": "<translated word>",
      "to_lemma": "<lemma/base form of translated word>",
      "pos": "<part of speech: noun|verb|adjective|adverb|pronoun|preposition|conjunction|interjection|article|other>",
      "difficulty": "<CEFR level: A1|A2|B1|B2|C1|C2>",
      "from_definition": "<context-appropriate definition of the word based on how it's used in this story>"
    }
  ]
}

IMPORTANT:
- Include EVERY meaningful word from the original story (exclude common articles and pronouns unless pedagogically valuable)
- Ensure 'from_definition' is context-specific to how the word is used in this particular story
- Use standard part-of-speech tags
- Assign difficulty levels based on word complexity and CEFR standards
- Return ONLY valid JSON, no additional text or markdown formatting

